Our Hokusai x Tsuki white hoodie features a cuckoo from Japanese artist Katsushika Hokusai's Cuckoos and Azalea (ca 1828) with a Japanese inscription of a poem by Chinese poet Yang Wanli on the arms and front.. ending with azaleas on both wrists!

Shop this style for $75 USD at the link in our bio 🔗 #tsukimarket

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tsuki 月 on August 20, 2021.

node.text:
Why hang art on a wall when you can wear it instead? 🖼

Our Hokusai x Tsuki collection features prints by Katsushika Hokusai a Japanese artist, ukiyo-e painter, and printmaker of the Edo period. Our black hoodie features this print, Cuckoos and Azalea, on the left chest. 

See the entire collection at the link in our bio. If you have any questions about your order, sizing, styling, etc. you can tap the email button in our bio too! #tsukimarket

Have you checked out our Hokusai x Tsuki collection yet? 

Our crewneck features Cuckoos and Azalea (ca 1828), one of Hokusai’s nature scenes with a Japanese inscription of a poem by Chinese poet Yang Wanli, it has been dissected into separate pieces across the front chest and sleeves.

This collection ships mid August. If you have any questions about styling, sizing, your order, etc. click the email button in our bio to get in touch with a member of our customer experience team! #tsukimarket
